  "type": "Exercise",
  "number": "13.4.6.14",
  "title": "",
  "body": "  Projectile Motion: The -value of an object moving under the principles of projectile motion is . A particular projectile is fired with an initial velocity of ft\/s and an angle of elevation of . It travels a distance of ft in 3 seconds.  Is the projectile more sensitive to errors in initial speed or angle of elevation?   Distance of the projectile is a function of two variables (leaving ): . The total differential of is . The coefficient of has a much greater magnitude than the coefficient of , so a small change in the angle of elevation has a much greater effect on distance traveled than a small change in initial velocity.  "
